-- Ontario Teachers’ Fund Planning Asia Expansion, Independent Says
-- B y   M i c h e l l e   W i e s e   B o c k m a n n
-- 2012-06-03T15:48:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/ontario-teachers-fund-planning-asia-expansion-independent-says.html
The  Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan ,
the owner of Camelot Group Plc that operates the U.K.’s National
Lottery, plans to expand into  Asia , the Independent on Sunday
 reported , citing an unidentified industry source.  An action plan for Asia is at the proposal stage for the
$117 billion pension fund that operates out of London, New York
and Toronto, according to the newspaper. The fund has some
investments in China, India and Japan and sees Asia as a major
area of growth, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michelle Wiese Bockmann in London at 
 mwiesebockma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alaric Nightingale at 
 anightingal1@bloomberg.net  